CONTEXT MinimalAmbiguity IN ENGLISH

CLASSIFY S ISA G

RELATION r[S*C]
RELATION r[G*C]

-- Trigger the ambiguity by using the composition in a rule
RULE testAmbiguity0: I[S] ; r
RULE testAmbiguity1: I[G] ; r
MEANING "This should trigger the ambiguous signature error"

ENDCONTEXT
{-
With RULE testAmbiguity: I[S] ; r  we get:
  Ambiguous signatures of the composition of I[S] and r. You might mean one of: 
      -   I[S] ; r with result [S*C]
      -   I[S] ; r with result [S*C]
  
  Type analysis:
  [S*C], [S*C] I[S];r[G*C], I[S];r[S*C]
  [S]              ├── I[S]
  [G*C], [S*C]     └── r[G*C], r[S*C]

With RULE testAmbiguity: I[G] ; r  we get:
  Ambiguous signatures of the composition of I[G] and r. You might mean one of: 
      -   I[G] ; r with result [G*C]
      -   I[G] ; r with result [S*C]
  
  Type analysis:
  [G*C], [S*C] I[G];r[G*C], I[S];r[S*C]
  [G]              ├── I[G]
  [G*C], [S*C]     └── r[G*C], r[S*C]

Note that both ambiguities are very different, even though the ambiguity of r causes both:
In the first case, I[S] constrains the result, which is [S*C] in both options.
In the second case, I[G] does not constrain the result, but I is refined to S if r[S*C] is chosen.
-}